.34", "bbox": [288.5, 431.9, 675.4, 442.0]}, {"text": "K2O kg ha-1 <55 very low 3851.55 30.77", "bbox": [45.5, 445.8, 675.4, 458.7]}, {"text": "55–110 low 5154.92 41.19", "bbox": [284.9, 463.5, 675.4, 473.6]}, {"text": "110–280 medium 2726.93 21.19", "bbox": [282.5, 479.3, 675.4, 489.4]}, {"text": "280–500 high 411.43 1.67", "bbox": [282.5, 495.1, 675.4, 505.2]}, {"text": ">500 very high 371.53 2.60", "bbox": [288.5, 510.8, 675.4, 521.0]}, {"text": "Zn mg kg-1 <0.25 very low 12307.92 98.33", "bbox": [45.5, 524.7, 675.4, 536.7]}, {"text": "0.25–0.5 low 208.44 1.67", "bbox": [282.6, 542.5, 675.4, 552.6]}, {"text": "0.5–1.0 medium - -", "bbox": [285.0, 558.2, 609.2, 568.3]}, {"text": "1.0–2.0 high - -", "bbox": [285.0, 574.0, 609.2, 584.1]}, {"text": ">2.0 very high - -", "bbox": [289.7, 589.7, 609.2, 599.9]}, {"text": "B mg kg-1 <0.2 very low - -", "bbox": [45.5, 603.6, 609.2, 615.7]}, {"text": "0.2–0.5 low 6949.26 55.52", "bbox": [285.0, 621.3, 675.4, 631.4]}, {"text": "0.5–1.2 medium 5408.10 43.21", "bbox": [285.0, 637.2, 675.4, 647.3]}, {"text": "1.2–2.0 high - -", "bbox": [285.0, 652.9, 609.2, 663.0]}, {"text": ">2.0 very high 159 1.27", "bbox": [289.7, 668.6, 675.4, 678.8]}, {"text": "https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0206350.t004", "bbox": [45.5, 687.0, 236.3, 697.6]}, {"text": "soil pH. As the ammonium-N in fertilizers undergoes nitrification, hydrogen ions are released,", "bbox": [252.5, 721.0, 726.5, 733.6]}, {"text": "which can increase acidity [51], and Tripathi and Shrestha [52] reported an increase of acidity", "bbox": [252.5, 737.3, 722.3, 750.0]}, {"text": "up to 4.1 (in 2000) from 5.6 (in 1997) after the application of fertilizers at four locations in", "bbox": [252.5, 753.8, 702.2, 766.4]}, {"text": "western Nepal.", "bbox": [252.5, 770.2, 327.2, 782.8]}, {"text": "Plant growth and most soil processes are favored by a specific pH range. The low pH leads", "bbox": [267.6, 786.6, 718.6, 799.2]}, {"text": "to Al and Mn toxicity, along with deficiency and/or unavailability of plant nutrients such as", "bbox": [252.5, 803.0, 709.9, 815.6]}, {"text": "P, Ca, K, Mg, and Mo as observed by Dembele et al. [53] and Tisdale et al. [54]. To produce a", "bbox": [252.5, 817.3, 717.8, 833.5]}, {"text": "sustained crop growth and yield, efforts should be made to increase the pH, which can be", "bbox": [252.5, 835.8, 698.7, 848.5]}, {"text": "addressed through liming and OM management or adoption of the acid tolerant crops.", "bbox": [252.5, 852.2, 688.3, 864.9]}, {"text": "Soil organic matter. Soil OM was relatively low (1 to 2.5%) in the majority (48.8%) of the", "bbox": [267.6, 868.6, 723.0, 881.3]}, {"text": "study area, followed by very low (<1%) in 26.88% (Table 4 and Fig 3). The low organic content", "bbox": [252.5, 885.0, 727.2, 897.7]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0206350 October 26, 2018 11 / 20", "bbox": [45.5, 946.7, 727.3, 956.8]}]}